      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:40:1",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/40/749",
      "text": [
        " اَلصَّلاَةِ إِذَا دُبِغَ فَقَالَ «لاَ وَ إِنْ دُبِغَ سَبْعِينَ مَرَّةً."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.749 - Muhammad ibn Muslim narrated from Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) that he asked him about wearing the skin of a dead animal (carrion) during prayer if it has been tanned.\nImam (as) said: \"No, even if it has been tanned seventy times.\""
        ]
      }
